16:
But the God whom we Israelites worship is not like those idols;\q2 he is the one who created everything that exists;
\q1 we, the tribe of Israel, belong to him;
\q2 he is the commander of the angel armies.


\q1

20:
It is as though our great tent is destroyed;\q2 the ropes that held it up have been cut;
\q1 our children have gone away from us and will not return;
\q2 there are no people left to rebuild our great tent.


\q1
